  "text": "The error string 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates from the authoritative etcd source code. The ErrCompacted error variable is defined in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go at line 37 as 'var ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\")'. This is the source-of-truth error in the MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) storage layer. The rangeKeys function in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go at line 72 is the core function that returns this error when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction. Specifically, at line 80-82, rangeKeys checks if the requested revision (rev) is less than the compaction main revision (tr.s.compactMainRev), and if so, returns ErrCompacted. This check ensures clients cannot access data that has been removed during the compaction process."
}

